article.description: Hayden Graham scored 20 points and Trevor Lyons added 14 to lift Air Force past UC Davis 67-60 on Saturday.
article.headline: Air Force dispatches UC Davis in 67-60 victory
article.linkText: Air Force dispatches UC Davis in 67-60 victory
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. -- Hayden Graham scored 20 points and Trevor Lyons added 14 to lift Air Force past UC Davis 67-60 on Saturday. Graham was 8 of 11 from the floor with three 3-pointers. Lyons made 5 of 10 field goals and added five assists. Zach Moer chipped in 10 points for Air Force (7-4). Darius Graham led UC Davis (4-5) with 16 points, five assists and four steals. Nolan Berry made a 3-pointer and converted a 3-point play to pull UC Davis to 46-43 with 10:43 remaining. But the Falcons outscored the Aggies 11-6 over the next four minutes, capped by Graham's 3 to make it 57-49. Neither team scored over the next three minutes until Kyle Broekhuis made a 3-pointer to stretch the Falcons' lead to 60-49 with 3:44 left. The Aggies shot just 38 percent from the field and were 4 for 23 from 3-point range.
